<h2>Protection from the Elements</h2>
Our advanced aluminum weep system carries water and condensation away from the wood, which increases the longevity of the structure. A solid wood structure is typically utilized with smaller structures that have spans of 12‚Äô0‚Äù or less. Any span over 12‚Äô0‚Äù would be recommended to utilize glulam. A solid wooden structure is recommended for structures that are going to be stained, and glulam is used for painted structures.[/vc_column_text][/vc_column][vc_column width="1/3"][vc_column_text]
<h2><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-37357" src="https://solarinnovations.com/wp-content/uploads/wood-sunroom-residential.png" alt="" width="680" height="400" /></h2>
<h2>Staining</h2>
Owners can stain the structure themselves if they would like or Solar Innovations<sup>¬Æ</sup>¬†can complete the staining using a 3-5 coat microporous sealer. The first coat seals/protects the wood. The second coat stains the wood and the third coat is a finishing coat.¬†With the addition of decorative trims and other accessories, the potential of Solar Innovations<sup>¬Æ</sup>¬†wood systems are limitless.¬†It is the customer‚Äôs responsibility to properly maintain the finish on the wood to preserve the warranty.[/vc_column_text][/vc_column][/vc_row][vc_row][vc_column width="1/4"][vc_column_text]
